Preheat your oven to 220°C, fill and boil your #kettle{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat, season the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lay the chicken in the frying pan skin-side down.

Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}, then turn and cook for another ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Put the chicken on a #baking tray{}, skin-side up, roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{12-15%minutes}. Keep the frying pan, you'll need it again soon.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Potatoes and Spinach ==

Meanwhile, fill a large #saucepan{} with boiling water from your kettle and return to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and add to the saucepan.

Cook until you can easily slip a knife through them, ~{12-15%minutes}, adding the @baby spinach{100%g} for the final ~{1%minute} of cooking. Drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan with the lid on, off the heat.

== Chilli & Chive Sauce ==

While the potatoes cook, halve, deseed and finely chop the @red chilli{1/2}. Finely chop the @chives{1 bunch} (or use #scissors{}). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Return the frying pan to a medium heat (no need to wash it). Add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry.

When hot, add the chilli and garlic to the frying pan and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Add the water (see ingredients for amount) and @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} to the frying pan, bring to the boil and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2%minutes}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} into the frying pan along with three-quarters of the chives. Season to taste with pepper, then remove the frying pan from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When the chicken is almost cooked, gently reheat the sauce.

> TIP: Add a splash of hot water if it needs loosening.

Season the spinach and potatoes with a pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a knob of butter if you have any!

Divide the spinach and potatoes between your plates. Serve the chicken breast alongside and spoon the chilli and chive sauce all over. Finish with a sprinkling of remaining chives.